      "timestep_posted": 19
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid budget-friendly project with good bones and a driveline that still feels eager. Engine starts up, pulls through the rev range, and the transmission engages as it should. Not a show car, but a usable platform for someone who wants dependable transportation with room to sort cosmetics and deferred odds and ends. Suspension, braking, and steering feel serviceable, and it has the kind of straightforward mechanical layout that makes ownership approachable. If you want an inexpensive driver/project with real potential, this one is worth a look.",
